docstrings: * Utility Selenium class used exclusively by {@link SeleniumElementFinder} to provide {@link ExpectedCondition} implementations, just like {@link ExpectedConditions} do.

* Extends {@link ExpectedConditions#presenceOfElementLocated(By)} by returning the current focused element if by == null * * @param by instance o {@link By} representing an element selector * @return instance of {@link ExpectedCondition}

* Implements an {@link ExpectedCondition} which locates element attributes
	 *
	 * @param by instance o {@link By} representing an element selector
	 * @param attributeName Attribute name for the given element to be searched
	 * @return instance of {@link ExpectedCondition}

* Implements an {@link ExpectedCondition} which returns a boolean value indicating if the selector (and optionally an attribute) is present (or absent) in the page, depending of ensurePresence * argument * * @param by instance o {@link By} representing an element selector * @param attributeName Attribute name for the given element to be searched * @param ensurePresence if true checks if the element is present on the page. Otherwise checks if the element is absent of the page * @return instance of {@link ExpectedCondition}
